Our Reporter  No fewer than 10 million farmers nationwide have benefited from the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) Anchor Borrowers Programmes, National Deputy Secretary,Rice Farmers Association of Nigeria (RIFAN), Alhaji Iliyasu Awodi has said. Awodi made this known in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Abuja. It is intended to create a linkage between anchor companies involved in agro-processing and small holder farmers of the required key agricultural commodities.  Noting the benefits of the scheme to farmers, Awodi said that the multiplier effect of the programme was enormous. “More than 10 million are engaged through the programme nationwide and it has helped in job creation,’’ he said. 